\nThe structure story begins with the base that formed between roughly 0.8010 and 0.8035 through early July. That area absorbed repeated selling pressure across several sessions, with the 0.8033 structure support zone \u2014 touched twice \u2014 acting as the floor from which the current advance has launched. The recovery from that base has been methodical rather than explosive: a grind through the 0.8080s, a sharp impulsive session on 13 July that briefly tagged 0.8149 before pulling back, and then a second, more sustained leg higher beginning on 20 July. Yesterday's daily candle closed at 0.8144, the highest close in over a month, and today's session has so far extended that range marginally to 0.8148 before modest consolidation set in. The broader picture suggests the pair has transitioned from a range-bound, choppy regime into a tentative uptrend, with the bullish bias now supported by structure.\n\nOn the H1 chart, the intraday narrative is one of early Asian-session strength followed by a measured drift lower through the European morning. Price pushed to 0.8148 in the 03:00\u201305:00 UTC window before sellers absorbed the advance, nudging the pair back toward 0.8132\u20130.8134 by early afternoon. The hourly sequence of lower highs since 05:00 UTC is worth noting \u2014 it represents short-term consolidation rather than a structural reversal, but it does suggest the immediate momentum has stalled. The 0.8140\u20130.8148 band now acts as the near-term resistance cluster, representing the prior reaction zone from yesterday's high and this morning's peak.\n\nThe economic calendar carries no scheduled releases today, which removes a key source of exogenous volatility. In the absence of data catalysts, price action is likely to remain technically driven, with liquidity conditions potentially thinner than usual. That environment can either allow clean technical setups to play out or produce erratic, low-conviction moves \u2014 both scenarios deserve consideration.\n\nWhat would change the bullish read? A daily close back below the 0.8093 area \u2014 the base of the current three-day advance \u2014 would begin to undermine the structure. A more definitive invalidation would come from a sustained move beneath 0.8035, which would return price to the prior consolidation range and call the entire recovery into question. Until either of those levels is breached on a closing basis, the chart continues to favour the upside scenario.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}